  %section.description
    %p I am a <b>software professional</b> currently located in Skopje (Macedonia).
    %p I am an <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/it_com_mk/5003633679/in/set-72157624863051331/lightbox/" target="_blank">award-winning</a> Android <a href="https://market.android.com/details?id=mk.popravi.mobile&hl=en" target="_blank">mobile application</a> developer and Ruby on Rails open-source <a href="http://contributors.rubyonrails.org/contributors/dalibor-nasevic/commits" target="_blank">contributor</a>. I have been working in various capacities on numerous Ruby on Rails projects <a href="http://www.workingwithrails.com/person/13391-dalibor-nasevic" target="_blank">since 2007</a>.
    %p I am also <b>co-founder and organizer</b> of <a href="http://ruby.mk" target="_blank">MKRUG</a> (Macedonian Ruby Users Group) and active member of <a href="/posts/31-global-day-of-coderetreat-in-skopje-macedonia">software craftmenship</a> movement. I have given <a href="http://b10g.spodeli.org/search/label/ruby.mk" target="_blank">technical</a> presentations on web and mobile technologies, and <a href="http://blip.tv/esocietymk-2010/dalibor-nasevik-popravi-mk-4661075" target="_blank">non-technical</a> presentations on <a href="http://popravi.mk" target="_blank">PopraviMK</a> project in various venues.
    %p Currently, I am employed by <a href="http://www.siyelo.com/" target="_blank">Siyelo</a> - web application development consultancy with distributed teams in Cape Town and Skopje.
    %p I am highly motivated toward good execution. Tools like: Linux, Vim, Git and programming practices like: TDD/BDD and Pair Programming are my good friends. I have solid experience mentoring developers in local and distributed teams and experience with Agile methodologies like Scrum and XP.
    %p I have received B.Sc. in "Computer Engineering, Computer Science and Automatics" from <a href="http://www.feit.ukim.edu.mk/" target="_blank">FEIT</a> (Faculty of Electrical Engineering and Information Technologies) in Skopje.
    %p As a good engineer I enjoy building products from start to finish. Starting with an idea, researching new technologies, working on UI/UX interactions, developing & designing object-oriented software with best-practices and coding standards and finally deploying a working solution.
    %p <b>Get in touch with me</b>: <br />Email me at <a href="mailto:dalibor.nasevic@gmail.com">dalibor.nasevic@gmail.com</a>. Follow me on <a href="http://www.twitter.com/blackflasher" target="_blank">Twitter</a>.


